<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1905-02-05T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1905-02-05T00:00:00-05:00" n="71" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d71">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Beaupré</persName> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Buenos
                                        Aires</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1905-02-05"><hi rend="italic">February 5,
                                1905</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>(Mr. Beaupré reports that order has been restored in the city and that
                            business and traffic are approaching normal conditions. The indications
                            are that the government will be able to suppress the uprising without
                            difficulty. Telegrams and the press are controlled by the censor.)</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>